Durban - Residents living in an informal settlement in Dunbar Road, Cato Manor could do nothing this week as their shacks went up in flames  Their shacks caught alight on Wednesday night at the intersection of Borough and Dunbar Roads. EThekwini municipality spokesperson, Msawakhe Mayisela, said the Durban Fire and emergency services dispatched a team to this incident at 22h09. When they arrived they found the shacks well alight. "Five informal dwellings were razed by the fire. The fire was contained so that it did not spread to any formal houses. The fire department suspected illegal connection as the cause of the fire. One of the street light poles was also on fire. It took the team about 45 minutes to extinguish the blaze. ," Mayisela said. Mayisela said there were no injuries reported either to fire brigade staff or members of the public.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
